title: Four bodies recovered from Red Sea day after tourist boat capsizes
description: Five more rescued and seven still missing from the Sea Story, which was carrying 30 tourists and 14 crewEgyptian naval forces recovered four bodies and rescued five more people from the Red Sea a day after a large tourist boat sank in rough waters, officials have said. Seven people are still missing.The Red Sea governor, Amr Hanafi, said the yacht, called Sea Story, had been struck by high waves on Monday and sank in less than 7 minutes. Continue reading...

title: Israel-Hezbollah ceasefire: What it means for Lebanon’s future
description: A US-brokered ceasefire between Israel and Hezbollah is set to begin, halting over a year of fighting. The deal involves Israeli troop withdrawals and Hezbollah's retreat north of the Litani River, with UN peacekeepers deployed. While offering a reprieve, the agreement's fragility is underscored by the unresolved Gaza conflict and the broader Palestinian question.
author: TOI World Desk

title: Submerged car, human remains found in Georgia pond may solve 1980 New York couple disappearance
description: A submerged car found in a Georgia pond may solve the 44-year-old mystery of a missing New York couple. The vehicle matches the description of the car belonging to Charles and Catherine Romer, who disappeared in 1980. Personal belongings and a human bone were discovered inside, offering potential closure to their family.
author: TOI World Desk
